nd a partner company to download and upload blobs. Only your company is allowed to delete uploaded blobs. You need to secure the container. What should you do?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Create a stored access policy on the container with only Delete permissions. Create a shared access signature with all permissions.','Create a stored access policy on the container with all permissions. Create a shared access signature with only Read and Add permissions.','Create a stored access policy on the container with only Read and Add permissions. Create a shared access signature with all permissions.','Create a stored access policy on the container with only Delete permissions. Create a shared access signature with only Read and Add permissions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(545,'Choose the best answer.','You deploy an ASP.NET Core MVC application to Azure App Services. You enable and require Azure Active Directory (AD) authentication for the application. The following code exists: public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services) { services AddMvc(): services. AddAuthorization(options = &gt; { options. AddPolicy(“EmployeeOnly”, policy = &gt; policy. RequireClaim( &quot; Employeeld”)); }); } Employees have a claim named Employeeld in Azure AD. Contractors do not have this claim. You need to ensure that only employees can access a controller class named BenefitsController. Which attribute should you add to the BenefitsController class?','SINGLE_CHOICE','[Authorize(Policy= &quot;Empbyeeld”)]','[SecurityRole(Policy=”EmployeeOnly”)]','[SecurityRole(Policy=”Employeeld”)]','[Authorize(Policy=”EmployeeOnly”)]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'d','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(546,'Choose the best answer.','You have an on-premises web application that allows customers to access their bank accounts. You have a byte array variable named securityQuestions that represents security questions associated with a customer. Because of a recent data breach of unencrypted security questions and the corresponding social engineering attacks, you want to encrypt the security questions. You add a key named encryptionKey to a key vault named companyA. You create an instance of KeyVaultClient named client. You need to encrypt the securityQuestions byte array. Which code segment should you use?','SINGLE_CHOICE','client.EncryptAsync( &quot;companyA &quot;, &quot;encryptionKey=RSAOAEP256 &quot;, securityQuestions);','client.EncryptAsync( &quot;https://companyAvault.azure.net/encryptionKey &quot;, &quot;RSAOAEP256 &quot;, securityQuestions);','client.EncryptAsync( &quot;companyA/encryptionKey &quot;, &quot;RSAOAEP256 &quot;, securityQuestions);','client.EncryptAsync( &quot;https://vault.azure.ner, &quot;companyA/encryptionKey=RSAOAEP256 &quot;, securityQuestions);',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(547,'Choose the best answer.','You have the following code: var connectionString = GetAzureSq1DatabaseConnectIonString(); var policy = new RetryPolicy&lt; SqlDatabaseTransientErrorDetectionStrategy &gt; (3); using (var connection = new RellableSqlConnectIon(connectIonString, policy)) { connection. Open(); SqICommand cmd = new SqlCommand(“Update Customer Set Active=1”, connection); cmd. ExecuteNonQueryWithRetry(); } You need to determine what happens when this code runs and a connectivity error occurs. What should you conclude?','SINGLE_CHOICE','A connection attempt is tried every three seconds before a SqlException is thrown.','A connecnon attempt is tried three times before a SqlException is thrown.','A SqlException is thrown and the connection attempt is tried three seconds later','A SqlException is thrown and the connection attempt is tried three more times',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'d','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(548,'Choose the best answer.','You have the following code: String connectionString = GetConnectionString(); var obj = ConnectionMultiplexer. Connect(connectionString); var database = obj. GetDatabase(); var tables = database. StringGet( &quot; Tables &quot; ); You need to determine what this code does. What does this code retrieve?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Table names from an Azure table storage account','Data from an Azure Redis Cache','Rows from an easy table of an Azure Mobile','Documents from an Azure Cosmos DB database',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(549,'Choose the best answer.','You have an instance of IDatabase named database that represents a valid connection to an Azure Redis Cache. No items are currently stored in the cache. You need to determine the number of clients connected to the cache. Which code segment should you use?','SINGLE_CHOICE','var result = database.Ping(CommandFlags.FireAndForget);','var strearnInfo = database.StreamInfo( &quot;CLIENTS &quot;);','var clients = database.StringGet( &quot;connected_clients &quot;);','var info = database.Execute( &quot;INFO &quot;);',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'d','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(550,'Choose the best answer.','You have the following code In an ASP.NET web application: try { Save(): } Catch(Exception ex) { var client = new TelemetryClient(); client. TrackException(ex); } You need to determine where the exception gets logged. Where is the exception logged?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Event Log','The Trace.aspx page','Application Insights','Diagnostic trace listener',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'c','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(551,'Choose the best answer.','You deploy an ASP.NET web application to a development server on your company&#39; s corporate network. The web application will be accessed by users around the world. You need to capture performance metrics from multiple geographies before you move the application to a production server on the network. What should you do?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Configure a Load Balancer with multiple availability zones','Create HTTP redirection with Application Gateway.','Configure endpoint monitoring on a Traffic Manager profile.','Create a URL ping test in Application Insights',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'d','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(552,'Choose the best answer.','You are creating an Azure Logic App. The Logic App must use a Control action that emulates the following code: bool success = false; while (success == false) { success = CheckForNewOrders(); } You need to choose the appropriate Control action. Which Control action should you use?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Until','For each','Switch','Scope',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'a','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(553,'Choose the best answer.','The following class exists: class Book { public string Isbn (get; set; ); public string Title (get; set; ); public string Description (get; set; ); [IsFilterable] public decimal Price (get; set; ); } You write the following code to create an Azure Search Index: SearchServIceClient search = new SearchServiceClient(“cloudbnb”, credentials); search. indexes. Create(new Index() { Name = &#39; books &quot;, Fields = FieldBuilder. BulldForType&lt; Book &gt; () }); When this code runs, you receive an exception with the following message: Property Price has an unsupported type System. Decimal You need to change the type of the Price property to support Azure Search. Which type should you use?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Object','Float','System.Double','System.Single',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'c','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(554,'Choose the best answer.','You create an Azure API Management (APIM) gateway to expose a web API. You want to expose four new operations on the web API to selected users. You want to accomplish this without having to provide a different hostname to the users. You also want to test the operations without publishing them. You need to expose the new operations. What should you do?','SINGLE_CHOICE','Create a separate APIM gateway','Create a separate web API','Create a revision','Create a version',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'c','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(555,'Choose the best answer.','You have the following API Management (APIM) policy statements: &lt; rate-limit-by-key calls= &quot; 10 &quot; renewal-period= &quot; 60 &quot; counter-key= &quot; @(context. Request. IpAddress) &quot; / &gt; &lt; quota-by-key calls= &quot; 2000 &quot; bandwidth= &quot; 10000 &quot; renewal-period = &quot; 2629800 &quot; counter-key= &quot; @(context. Request. IpAddress) &quot; / &gt; What usage is allowed by these statements?','SINGLE_CHOICE','10 calls per second with up to 2,000 calls or 10,000 megabytes (MB) per month','10 calls per 60 days with up to 2,000 calls or 10,000 megabytes (MB) per month','10 calls per minute with up to 2,000 calls or 10,000 kilobytes (KB) per month','10 calls per 60 days with up to 2,000 calls or 10,000 kilobytes (KB) per year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'c','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(556,'Choose the best answer.','You plan to create a containerized web application for your company. You retrieve a Docker file from an online repository and build a container image from this file that is named apps. You need to deploy the image to an Azure Container Registry that is named companyireg. How should you complete the command? Choose the correct option.','SINGLE_CHOICE','docker push companylreg. kureczio /apps','az acr push companylreg. kureczio /apps','docker push companylreg. Azurewebsites.net /apps','az acr push companylreg. Azurewebsites.net /apps',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'a','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(557,'Choose the best answer.','You create a web application by using Visual Studio. You have a resource group named webapps-rg. You need to host this web application in Azure without incurring charges. How should you complete the Azure CLI commands? Choose two correct options','MULTIPLE_CHOICE','az appservice plan create --name webapps \\ --resource-group webapps-rg --sku free','az webapp create --name webapp1 \\ --resource-group webapps-rg --plan webapps','az app plan create --name webapps \\ --resource-group webapps-rg --plan free','az appservice create --name webapp1 \\ --resource-group webapps-rg --plan webapps',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'a::b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(558,'Choose the best answer.','You deploy a web application to Azure App Services. The web application is accessible at http: //mupwebapp. azurewebsites. net. The web application&#39; s code uses tracing to log verbose information. You want to enable diagnostic logging to meet the following requirements: • Download log files that contain error messages produced by the web application from http: //mupwebapp. scm. azurewebsites. net/apiMs/LogFiles/Application. • Log entries produced by the web application must use a space-separated format. • Download log files that contain HTTP errors from http: //mu pwebapp. scm. azurewebsites. net/apiMs/LogFiles/Detailed Errors. • Log entries that contain HTTP errors must reside in HTML files. You need to enable the appropriate diagnostic logging settings. You only want to enable the required settings. Which settings should you enable? For the following settings, select Yes if you are required to enable the setting. Otherwise, select No. Application Logging (Blob','SINGLE_CHOICE','Yes','No',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(559,'Choose the best answer.','You plan to use Azure Cosmos DB to store invoices. Details about each invoice are as follows: * Each invoice has a unique invoice number. This number is an alphanumeric character with a maximum length of 10. * Each invoice has an amount. The amount ranges from a decimal value of 1000 to a decimal value of 10, 000. There is no minimum or maximum number defined. * Each invoice is assigned to one project. There are seven projects to which an invoice can be assigned. * Each invoice has a date. Invoice dates are usually the end of the month. There can be any number of invoices that use the same date, but usually there are no more than two. You need to choose an appropriate partition key. Which partition key should you use? Choose the correct answer.','SINGLE_CHOICE','Number','Project','Date','Account',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11'),(560,'Choose the best answer.','You create an Azure Cosmos DB collection named receipts that represents business receipts. The collection is part of a Cosmos DB database named mup. No other databases or collections exist in the Cosmos DB account. A sample document is as follows: { &quot; id&#39; : &quot; 1001 &quot;, &quot; amount &quot;: 213. 13, &quot; vendor &quot;: &quot; MeasureUp &quot;, &quot; category &quot;: &quot; Lodging &quot;, &quot; date &quot;: &quot; 2019-03-01 &quot; } You need to write a query that returns all receipts where the category is Lodging. Which two queries would meet your goal? Each answer presents a complete solution. Choose the correct answers.','SINGLE_CHOICE','SELECT * FROM receipts WHERE Category = &quot;Lodging &quot;','SELECT * FROM root r WHERE r.Category = &quot;Lodging &quot;','SELECT * FROM root WHERE Category = &quot;Lodging &quot;','SELECT • FROM receipts r WHERE r.Category = &quot;Lodging &quot;',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'b','','2023-02-14 14:50:11','2023-02-14 14:50:11');
